-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527826\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527826\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gfb1665703181522.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gfb1665703181522.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gfb1665703181522.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gfb1665703181522\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When transferring large amounts of data, for example, when uploading or downloading\n    files, the UHTTP component enables you to optimize the TCP/IP connection.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gfb1665703181522__section_k24_l3w_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d547852e50\">TCP/IP Connection</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The UHTTP component recognizes the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"Connection: Keep-Alive\"</code> header for\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SEND</span> requests. When this header is present, it will attempt to use the\n        same TCP/IP connection, as long as successive calls to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SEND</span> operation\n        all go to the same host. This is useful when transferring large amounts of data, for example\n        when uploading or downloading files.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">You can set the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Connection</code> header by adding it to a Uniface list, using\n        the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104gfb1665703181522_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"gfb1665703181522__codeblock_ypm_n3w_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">putitem/id/case vHeaders, \"Connection\", \"Keep-Alive\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">On the first appearance of the header, a new connection is made. While the header continues\n        to be present and the same server host is used, the same connection will be used on\n        successive calls to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SEND</span> operation. If the header is removed or a new\n        server host is specified, a new connection is initialized and used.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gfb1665703181522__section_bkt_q3w_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d547852e83\">Socket Buffer Size</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The TCP socket buffer sizes are set when a socket has been created and before a connection\n        is made. They do not change while the same connection is being re-used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">To enhance performance when uploading or downloading files, you can increase the default\n        TCP socket buffer size using options on the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS</span> and\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DUMP_FILE_CONTENTS</span> operations. For example, if a file is uploaded and\n        then one is downloaded from the same server and the<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"Connection: Keep-Alive\"</code>\n        header is used, the same connection may be used throughout. In this case, you could consider\n        setting both the send and receive TCP buffers using the options <code class=\"ph codeph\">TCPSNDBUF</code>\n        and <code class=\"ph codeph\">TCPRCVBUF</code> in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS</span> operation, so\n        that the receive buffer is set for the download.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unt1665702546031.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SEND</a><p>Send an HTTP request.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/duc1665702546482.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS</a><p>Load a file, or part of a file, into the body of an HTTP request in preparation for uploading to a REST-compliant API.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eip1665702546644.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DUMP_FILE_CONTENTS</a><p>Declare the response to be destined for a file, or receive a file or a part thereof, in the body of a response as a download from a REST API.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527826\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527826\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UHTTP and the TCP/IP Connection Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 When transferring large amounts of data, for example, when uploading or downloading files, the UHTTP component enables you to optimize the TCP/IP connection. TCP/IP Connection The UHTTP component recognizes the \"Connection: Keep-Alive\" header for SEND requests. When this header is present, it will attempt to use the same TCP/IP connection, as long as successive calls to the SEND operation all go to the same host. This is useful when transferring large amounts of data, for example when uploading or downloading files. You can set the Connection header by adding it to a Uniface list, using the following command: Explain this code putitem/id/case vHeaders, \"Connection\", \"Keep-Alive\" Copy On the first appearance of the header, a new connection is made. While the header continues to be present and the same server host is used, the same connection will be used on successive calls to the SEND operation. If the header is removed or a new server host is specified, a new connection is initialized and used. Socket Buffer Size The TCP socket buffer sizes are set when a socket has been created and before a connection is made. They do not change while the same connection is being re-used. To enhance performance when uploading or downloading files, you can increase the default TCP socket buffer size using options on the LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS and DUMP_FILE_CONTENTS operations. For example, if a file is uploaded and then one is downloaded from the same server and the \"Connection: Keep-Alive\" header is used, the same connection may be used throughout. In this case, you could consider setting both the send and receive TCP buffers using the options TCPSNDBUF and TCPRCVBUF in the LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS operation, so that the receive buffer is set for the download. Related Links SEND Send an HTTP request. LOAD_FILE_CONTENTS Load a file, or part of a file, into the body of an HTTP request in preparation for uploading to a REST-compliant API. DUMP_FILE_CONTENTS Declare the response to be destined for a file, or receive a file or a part thereof, in the body of a response as a download from a REST API. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}